comment:
* This class implements an optimized iterator for
 * "." patterns, that is, the self axes without any predicates.  
 * @see org.apache.xpath.axes.LocPathIterator
 * @xsl.usage advanced

methods.name: public int nextNode()
methods.comment: * Returns the next node in the set and advances the position of the * iterator in the set. After a NodeIterator is created, the first call * to nextNode() returns the first node in the set. * * @return The next Node in the set being iterated over, or * null if there are no more members in that set.

methods.name: public int asNode(XPathContext xctxt) throws javax.xml.transform.TransformerException
methods.comment:
* Return the first node out of the nodeset, if this expression is 
   * a nodeset expression.  This is the default implementation for 
   * nodesets.  Derived classes should try and override this and return a 
   * value without having to do a clone operation.
   * @param xctxt The XPath runtime context.
   * @return the first node out of the nodeset, or DTM.NULL.

methods.name: public int getLastPos(XPathContext xctxt)
methods.comment:
* Get the index of the last node that can be itterated to.
   * This probably will need to be overridded by derived classes.
   *
   * @param xctxt XPath runtime context.
   *
   * @return the index of the last node that can be itterated to.

methodNames: public int asNode(XPathContext xctxt) throws javax.xml.transform.TransformerException
